<subSubSection lastPageId="57" lastPageNumber="372" pageId="56" pageNumber="371" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="56.[831,1437,1793,2079]" pageId="56" pageNumber="371">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[831,945,1794,1818]" pageId="56" pageNumber="371">Remarks:</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus box="[1010,1056,1794,1818]" pageId="56" pageNumber="371">type</typeStatus>
specimens (a male and a female from 
<collectingCountry box="[899,967,1826,1849]" name="Brazil" pageId="56" pageNumber="371">Brazil</collectingCountry>
) of this species were not found in the 
<collectionCode box="[831,914,1859,1882]" pageId="56" pageNumber="371">BMNH</collectionCode>
, but the 
<typeStatus box="[1023,1080,1859,1883]" pageId="56" pageNumber="371">types</typeStatus>
of synonyms 
<emphasis box="[1248,1342,1858,1881]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="371">dotatalis</emphasis>
Walker, 
<emphasis box="[831,941,1891,1914]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="371">suffectalis</emphasis>
Walker, 
<emphasis box="[1058,1170,1891,1914]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="371">abruptalis</emphasis>
Walker, and 
<emphasis box="[1342,1436,1891,1914]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="371">dircealis</emphasis>
Walker are all there. This is the first record of this species for the 
<collectingRegion box="[994,1107,1956,1979]" country="Ecuador" name="Galapagos" pageId="56" pageNumber="371">Galápagos</collectingRegion>
archipelago, where specimens have been collected in 
<date box="[1120,1304,1988,2013]" pageId="56" pageNumber="371" value="2004" valueMax="2005">2004 and 2005</date>
. The three available specimens match the original description and 
<collectionCode box="[882,962,2055,2078]" pageId="56" pageNumber="371">BMNH</collectionCode>
<typeStatus box="[974,1031,2055,2079]" pageId="56" pageNumber="371">types</typeStatus>
of the synonyms mentioned above.
</paragraph>
